ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

Food Responsiveness Score
Notes: Level of food responsiveness with higher scores meaning greater response

ElementDescription: Emotional Over-Eating Score
Notes: Level of emotional eating with higher scores meaning more emotional eating

ElementDescription: Enjoyment of Food Scale
Notes: Level of food enjoyment with higher scores meaning more enjoyment

ElementDescription: Desire to Drink Scale
Notes: Level of desire to drink with higher scores meaning more desire

ElementDescription: Satiety Responsiveness
Notes: Level of satiety responsiveness with higher scores meaning more responsive

ElementDescription: Slowness in Eating Scale
Notes: Level of slowness of eating with higher scores meaning slower eating

Notes: Level of emotional undereating with higher scores meaning more undereating
